Part-time job in the summer vacation

•	Teaching English to student of the ninth grade and tenth grade;
•	The contents included textbook, and systematic grammar teaching, oral English skills and reading skills.

•	Supporting the general manager in organizing a variety of events, such as seminars, workshops, charity parties, Christmas parties to promote the interactions within the chamber and outside the chamber;
•	Conducting researches of current European companies or joint ventures in the north-eastern region of China to invite potential members;
•	Supporting membership management by managing their information and keep our members in touch and informed of what is going on in the chamber;
•	Necessary English-Chinese translation or vice versa as an interpreter and translator;
•	Administration work like reimbursements.
